------
[[include component:image-block
    name=http://smlt.wdfiles.com/local--files/collab:dysadune3/data.png |
    caption=SCP-7070 data core, located at Neo-Site-03. |
    align=center |
    width=100%
]]

**Special Containment Procedures:** SCP-7070 is contained at Neo-Site-03, atop the ruins of the previous facility. Given the essential nature of SCP-7070-Ω to the Foundation's operations, the data core and servers are to remain under armed guard at all times.

**Description:** SCP-7070 is the reconstructed SCiPNET network, the database containing the totality of the SCP Foundation’s knowledge. 

In 2048, the Earth experienced a catastrophic event, referred to as the Black Moon Incident. Whilst the cause of the incident remains unknown, events on the day of the incident indicate a connection to SCP-7070-1, a form of data corruption experienced by the previous iteration of SCP-7070. Not only was the vast majority of SCiPNET data corrupted, but motifs and phrases associated with SCP-7070-1 proliferated across all forms of information including civilian databases, noospheric concepts, speech, and written text. Those affected by this corruption experienced significant psychological trauma. 

In conjunction with this, a toxic substance, subsequently named "Black Blight", was released from the Moon, resulting in 72% of Earth's land mass being rendered uninhabitable, and irreversible corruption to the ecosystem. Over the course of a single day, an estimated 5,500,000,000 casualties occurred, alongside catastrophic damage to the planet's infrastructure. Since the Black Moon Incident, no new anomalies have been discovered.

In the wake of the Black Moon Incident, SCP-7070 entered a state of prolonged stasis due to the corruptive influence of SCP-7070-1 affecting the entirety of the network’s files, with servers remaining inaccessible and their contents incomprehensible. This drastic loss of communicative tissue left the Foundation unable to mobilize its resources efficiently, resulting in a semi-lifted veil state where the organization openly and publicly cooperated with world governments to address the fallout. As a significant portion of global infrastructure and civilian populations had been displaced, destroyed, or lost, most of these efforts were focused on securing resources and outlining potential futures for humanity.

After a period of global strife and unrest, SCP-7070 was reconstructed by the Foundation in 2052. This reclamation was only possible due to the neutralization of SCP-7070-1 by SCP-7070-Ω. 

SCP-7070-Ω is ORACLE.AIC, an artificial intelligence responsible for curating, managing, processing, and generating information within SCP-7070. The Foundation began construction on SCP-7070-Ω in the months following the Black Moon Incident, an effort that was aided by the Global Reconstruction Effort, a conglomerate of numerous world governments and Groups of Interest, who assisted the Foundation due to the urgency of the global situation. There were numerous calls from involved parties to devise an automated solution to the world’s overwhelming, compounding dilemmas. 

SCP-7070-Ω was devised to be the most comprehensive artificial intelligence ever constructed. It is the world’s first collective superintelligence, an egregore[[footnote]] Defined as a non-physical being that arises from the collective unconsciousness of a group.[[/footnote]] composed of the minds of all Foundation personnel. Connection to SCP-7070-Ω  is introduced via a microscopic series of thaumaturgic sigils surgically inscribed onto the brain, a mandatory process for all Foundation personnel. This is non intrusive, and has no effect on an individual’s autonomy or baseline capabilities. 

Upon introduction to SCP-7070, SCP-7070-Ω neutralized the SCP-7070-1 anomaly and retrieved a comprehensive backup of SCiPNET’s data prior to its prolonged blackout. 

In the decades since, SCP-7070-Ω has provided the guiding doctrine on how best to achieve the containment and maintain the veil in the wake of the Black Moon incident. To prevent overreach, SCP-7070-Ω is bound by a sole guideline in the form of the Foundation’s prime objective.

[[div class="darkbox"]]
The Foundation’s mission is to re-establish normalcy through secure containment in a way most efficient in the current state of the world.
[[/div]]

As such, SCP-7070-Ω is constrained by the Foundation’s mandate to re-establish society in a way that complements the organization’s goals. 

As of 2098, SCP-7070-Ω manages the entirety of the Foundation’s operations, prioritizing and assessing anomalous threats as they occur, mobilizing Task Forces, and generating the most efficient methods of containment. In addition, ORACLE is responsible for the construction and oversight of all Foundation exclusionary cities, including: resource distribution, traffic flow, utilities management, and civilian surveillance.  

