The following partial transcript is a speech given by O5-13 during a Global Reconstruction Effort conference in 2052, held at Neo-Site-19 shortly following its establishment:
[[div class="darkbox"]]

//[O5-13 stands at a podium in an open-air section of Neo-Site-19. Multiple high-ranking members of the Global Reconstruction Effort are seated behind her, including remaining members of the Overseer Council, ORACLE Head Technician Thomas Holden, and world leaders from various countries. There are hundreds of Foundation personnel present, the majority of which are armed and outfitted in military gear.]//

**O5-13:** Thank you all for being here. I’m grateful we could hold this ceremony today amidst all of the… multitudes of pressing duties that would require us elsewhere.

My name is Sophia Light. I am O5-13. At one point in time revealing your identity as an Overseer was tantamount to treason. It still is. But on paper, the Foundation is still an organization dedicated to containing the anomalous, upholding a curtain to the rest of the world. For all the progress we’ve made, and the sacrifices that have occured over the past four years, one fact remains: the Foundation failed. 

//[Silence. Some members of the Reconstruction Effort look at O5-13 with confusion.]//

**O5-13:** If we hadn’t failed, we would not be sitting underneath a bleeding sky, or be using empty containment cells for supply storage and shelter. We wouldn’t have to cope with the knowledge that our loved ones have succumbed to the Black Blight, living like animals in the desolate wastes that surround our encampments. This is not what I was asked to say today, but we failed. And in the face of that failure, there still remains, however childish, a hope that we may bounce back. That we can hit a switch and return like //that//. Trust me, we tried. There’s a screaming sinkhole where Yellowstone used to be now.

During the initial fallout, governments and organizations approached the Foundation, begging us to do something. They knew we had exhausted all of our resources, but they still asked. They came to us because of an idea. The idea of the Foundation, an organization which had miraculously succeeded against impossible odds for over a century. How could that Foundation fix this?

We were asked to create something that could coexist alongside and above us, to embody the tenants that we hold inside of us without placing responsibility in the hands of a select few. And so, I would like to unveil the Foundation’s ark, humanity’s life raft. A project that has been pushed into completion as it is our last possible option— the ORACLE collective superintelligence. Chances are, you’ve worked on completing it. Chances are, you’re already a part of it. 

This is our last chance. ORACLE will, ideally, eliminate the factor of chance from the global equation entirely. It will efficiently chart a course for the world’s future, and how best to achieve it. As Foundation personnel, consider your mandatory participation a penance to reconcile with the past. 

We are not accepting transfers or resignations from the organization for the foreseeable future. I believe you understand our reasoning. 

I know you never asked for any of this. 

//[O5-13 exits the stage. She is visibly upset.]//

//[The crowd is silent.]//
[[/div]]
