**Response:** Utilizing its predictive analytic capabilities, ORACLE.AIC estimated the location, status, and threat level of all anomalies extant in the records which survived the Black Moon Incident.[[footnote]] Currently estimated at 45%. [[/footnote]]  

In addition to this, ORACLE opined on a topic not explicitly specified in the problem statement. It stated that the Foundation could not resume containment efforts in the same manner as before the Black Moon Incident. Research should be scaled back in favour of pure containment, given the fragile state of both the Foundation and the world.

**Outcome:** Suggested strategy adopted. Recontainment efforts progressed with increased levels of success. The majority of anomalies suffer from Black Blight, experiencing an overall degradation of their properties: anomalies previously capable of locomotion are immobile, levels of sentience and sapience have decreased, and the effect of anomalous capabilities has waned or changed.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]
